just_use demo_board_move.py

# label: EARLY
# role: tight-feedback harness for tuning board-to-board drag physics

A one-move demo that creates a fresh session, executes a single
long-diagonal `move_stack` with an exaggerated-pace eased path,
and prints the replay URL. Purpose: let Steve eyeball the drag
physics in isolation instead of inside the noise of a full
40-action agent game.

## Surface

- `python3 games/lynrummy/python/demo_board_move.py`
- `--pace N` — ms per pixel (higher = slower / more
  exaggerated). Defaults to 10.

## Parameters (tuned by feel)

- Source: stack index 5 in the initial board (the 2C-3D-4C-
  5H-6S-7H 6-run).
- Target: board-frame `(500, 450)` — bottom-right corner,
  clear of all initial stacks.
- Distance: ~608 px diagonal.

## Pointers

- `gesture_synth.synthesize` — accepts `ms_per_pixel` kwarg for
  the demo to override the production default.
- `auto_player.py` — has its own cosmetic opener with a
  similar shape but baked into every new session.
